The Personal Assistant to Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu, Faruk Enabo and his friends have donated 20 vehicles to the All Progressives Congress (APC) campaign committee ahead of the 2019 general elections in Kebbi State. The donation was made during the flag off  of President Muhammadu Buhari and Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu 2019 campaign at the Haliru Abdu Stadium in Birnin Kebbi. Also, 18 Hajj seats were promised to members of the Kebbi State Association of Musicians for their support to the APC campaign across the 21 local government areas of the state. While addressing the APC supporters, Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu and the State  Chairman of APC, Alhaji Bala Sani Kangiwa promised President Muhammadu Buhari massive votes in the 2019 Presidential election in Kebbi State. Bagudu assured women and youths in the state of his government’s commitment to improve their lives through the various empowerment schemes. He added that his government would give more opportunities to women to serve in the state. He said “We have the highest number of women in government in the whole North west. We will continue to do more for them”, he said.  Presidential election: Bagudu promise Buhari highest votes in Kebbi Re-election campaign for Buhari, Bagudu kicks off as APC receives PDP ex-national treasurer BREAKING: PDP ex-National Treasurer, Buhari Bala, 4 LG chairmen join APC in Kebbi